Job Description:
The Regional Administrator works under the collaborative direction and supervision of the Chief Nursing Officer and manages a number of site Dialysis Programs (partial state, state-wide or collection of states). The Regional Administrator is accountable for the administrative/clinical activities, and quality outcomes of their business area. This includes the clinical operations, compliance, strategic planning, budget/billing/revenue cycle, and recruitment. The Regional Administrator ensures that all End Stage Renal Disease (ESRD) federal, state and ESRD regulatory standards are maintained at all times. This position also coordinates program/services with other local/state agencies to ensure integration of various programs and services throughout the communities and regions served and ensures staff is trained and able to provide service 24/7.

The Regional Administrator works with staff and providers to ensure staff are appropriately trained and licensed and that each facility is compliant with state and federal regulations.

PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITES:

1) Administrative
Oversees facility operations to ensure high quality of care, staff education/development and compliance;
Develops and implements plans to assure continuous improvement; and
Acts as a resource for staff regarding patient medical issues;
2) Communications
Encourages, monitors and participates in systems of communications with site leadership and physicians;
Holds regularly scheduled regional leadership meetings;
Alerts Medical Director and CNO of non-compliance situations beyond his/her control;
Follows and role models the Dialyze Direct Principles of Behavior;
Prepares and submits weekly leadership compliance reports: and
Attends regional QAPI and governing body meetings.
3) Management Resources/Staff
Supports sites to ensure they are adequately staffed to provide patient care based on census; and
Oversees overtime usage.

4) Performs similar or related duties as requested or directed.

JOB REQUIREMENTS:

Education
BA/BS required (relevant work experience may be accepted in lieu of degree).

Experience
Five years management experience in a Renal Dialysis program required; and
Project management experience preferred.

Skills
Knowledge of strategic business planning, budgets, revenue cycle, financial metrics, resource allocation, and management/leadership;
Strong analytical skills;
Able to function at a high-level with little operational oversight;
Exemplary interpersonal skills; able to effectively communicate (both verbal and written) with diverse backgrounds and different levels in the organization;
Able to define problems and identify solutions;
Able to present data in various formats to a variety of audiences;
Change agent;
Able to influence and develop collaborative, sustainable relationships;
Able to adapt to changing priorities and meet specific objectives under time constraints.

LICENSES, CERTIFICATIONS:

Current BLS certification required;
Valid State Nursing license; and
Valid driver’s license.

PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:

Able to sit and work at computer for extended periods of time;
Walk, sit, lift no more than 25 pounds;
Must be able to differentiate colors: and
Must be willing to travel to network facilities and sites as needed.

